i have been looking for a home made bread recipe without using a bread machine plain old fashioned white fluffy bread the recipes i've gotten a hold of seem to be too salty or no flavor at all thanks in advance so far i have baked two batches of the perfect white bread recipe by jim and i can't thank you enough i'm baking for a four man crew of commercial fishermen and got good reviews have'nt been able to test it myself though as they took it all i will continue with trying the other recipes donated thank you all for sending them in perfect white bread two loaves of bread crisp of crust and tender of crumb pkg active dry yeast c lukewarm water tbsp sugar tsp salt c crisco c hot milk to c enriched flour soften yeast in cup of the lukewarm water for minutes then stir until blended measure sugar salt and crisco into mixing bowl pour hot milk over them and stir mashing crisco against sides of bowl until broken into small lumps add remaining water and cool to lukewarm stir in cup flour add yeast and more cups flour and beat with a wooden spoon until batter is smooth and elastic stir in to cups more flour then with floured fingers work in enough additional flour to make a soft dough that does not stock to the fingers turn dough onto lightly floured board and knead for minutes about kneading strokes shape dough into a ball and put it in a bowl rubbed with crisco spread surface of dough lightly with crisco cover with a towel and let dough rise until double in bulk about hours punch dough down and turn onto floured board cut dough in half and shape each half into a smooth ball shape each ball into a loaf and put into bread pan rubbed with crisco cover pans with a towel and let bread rise until the sides of the raised bread reach the top of the pans and the center is nicely rounded above it about hour to bake bake loaves at degrees for to minutes or until golden brown when baked turn loaves from pans immediately to keep crust crisp and cool on a cake rack for a soft tender crust brush loaves with crisco as soon as they come from oven for one loaf of perfect bread and one dozen rolls make perfect white bread and let rise until double in bulk punch down dough and divide in half shape one half into a loaf and follow directions for rising and baking divide remaining dough into twelve portions and shape each portion into a round roll place rolls inches apart on baking sheet rubbed with crisco cover and let rise until double in bulk about hours bake at degrees for minutes or until done jean i think you will like this recipe jim b Idli Dim sum Flour Tortilla Mantou Breadmaker Hot dog Tofu Tea Muffin Cookware and bakeware Experiment Baked Alaska Naan Dairy Bengali cuisine Shewbread Coffee Chocolate Pasta Barbecue Potato chips Casting Cake Cooking weights and measures Cheese Ice cream Sourdough Plastic Cheesecake Pottery Pumpernickel bread French fries Textile manufacturing Mooncake D__ner kebab Baking Potato Dosa Mattress Drill bit Knife Brioche Violin Haggis Cuisine of Singapore Rum Halva Cuisine of Malaysia Yeast (baking) Fried chicken Hamster Tamale Souffl__ Table tennis Baklava Wine making Fried dough foods Cold Stone Creamery Beer Vinegar Chocolate Salty Balls Upholstery Domesticated turkey Internal ballistics Cajun cuisine Alcoholic beverage Chowder Milkshake Bong Sandwich Yoghurt Steel Softball Ramen Honey Soul food Meatloaf Sauna 